I think im following now on the current thinking for the how the api needs to feed the display. The podium will resolve an id that relates to a story, that story may or may not have an initiative that it will pull information for. It may or may not have children stories that it will resolve the data for. then that set of data with its needed display layout based on the data provided. This will allow for the initiative to be displayed, the story and whatever rotation through children stories. There will also be messaging from the podium that will cause updates to this display to occur as they interact TBD. Does this sound like what i need? a dataset of all the data relating to what should be shown so it can be displayed, then expect updates to manipulate that data as the presenter interacts on the podium?
